==Covers and tributes==
''The Duran Duran Tribute Album'', a 1997 collection of [[cover version]]s, included the following tracks from ''Rio'':
* "Rio", by [[ska punk]] band [[Goldfinger (band)|Goldfinger]]
* "The Chauffeur", by [[The Deftones]]
* "Hungry Like the Wolf", by [[Reel Big Fish]]
* "Hungry Like the Wolf", by 13 Winters
* "Save a Prayer", by  [[Eve's Plum]]
* "New Religion", by [[Jimmy Eat World]]
* "Save a Prayer", by [[Tony Hadley]]

Other covers include:
* "The Chauffeur", by [[Tre Lux]]
* German [[happy hardcore]] band [[Dune (German band)|Dune]] recorded "Save a Prayer" with the [[London Session Orchestra]] for their 1998 cover album ''[[Forever and Ever (Dune album)|Forever and Ever]]''
* American electronic pop musical project [[Sleepthief]] covered "The Chauffeur", sung by [[Kirsty Hawkshaw]], on its 2006 debut album ''The Dawnseeker''.

